# {{.Name}}

A Go application project built with [Forge](https://github.com/reliant-labs/forge). Use it for Connect RPC services, background workers, frontends, or CLI-first tools.

## Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
task deps
```

### 2. Add a component
```bash
forge add service myservice
forge add worker cleanup --kind cron --schedule "0 * * * *"
forge add frontend mobile --kind mobile
```

If you created the project with an initial service, define your proto by editing `proto/services/myservice/v1/myservice.proto`:
```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

package myservice.v1;

option go_package = "{{.Module}}/gen/myservice/v1;myservicev1";

service MyService {
  rpc SayHello(HelloRequest) returns (HelloResponse);
}

message HelloRequest {
  string name = 1;
}

message HelloResponse {
  string message = 1;
}
```

### 3. Generate code from protos
```bash
forge generate
```

### 4. Build and run
```bash
task build
task dev
```

## CLI Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `forge new` | Create a new project |
| `forge add service <name>` | Add a Go service |
| `forge add worker <name>` | Add a background worker; use `--kind cron --schedule "..."` for scheduled workers |
| `forge add frontend <name>` | Add a Next.js frontend app; use `--kind mobile` for React Native |
| `forge generate` | Generate code from proto files |
| `forge lint` | Lint proto and Go code |
| `forge build` | Build the project |
| `forge run` | Run the dev environment |
| `forge deploy <env>` | Deploy to an environment |
| `forge test` | Run tests |
| `forge db` | Database commands |

## Task Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `task deps` | Install Go (and frontend) dependencies |
| `task build` | Build Go binaries (and frontend bundle) |
| `task test` | Run Go + frontend tests (e2e is excluded via `-tags=e2e`) |
| `task test:e2e` | Run end-to-end tests (requires docker compose) |
| `task lint` | Run `golangci-lint`, `buf lint`, and frontend lint |
| `task dev` | Start dev infra and Air hot-reload |
| `task dev-up` | Bring up local dev infra with `app-debug` (Delve on :2345) |
| `task dev-up-prod` | Bring up local dev infra with the production `app` image |
| `task dev-down` | Tear down local dev infra (`docker compose --profile '*' down`) |
| `task proto` | Generate protobuf code via `buf generate` |
| `task clean` | Clean generated files and build artifacts |

Run `task --list` (or just `task`) at any time to see the full set of
automation entry points the scaffold ships with.

### App vs app-debug

`docker-compose.yml` defines two app variants that share the same env
vars and DB:

- **`app`** — production-style build; smaller image, no debugger. Runs
  by default with `docker compose up` and `task dev-up-prod`.
- **`app-debug`** — Delve-enabled build listening on `:2345`; gated
  behind the `debug` docker compose profile. Runs with `task dev-up`
  (the default dev story) so you can attach a debugger from your IDE.

If you don't need breakpoints, `task dev-up-prod` gives you a faster
cold start and a smaller image. `task dev-down` tears down both.

## End-to-end tests

The scaffold emits an `e2e/` tree gated behind the `e2e` Go build tag so
plain `go test ./...` and `task test` do **not** pull it in. Run it
explicitly:

```bash
task test:e2e
# or directly:
go test -tags=e2e -v -count=1 -timeout=20m ./e2e/...
```

CI runs e2e in its own workflow (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`) so the
fast PR workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) never blocks on docker
compose standing up. On pull requests the e2e job is gated behind the
`run-e2e` label (add the label to opt in); pushes to `main` and manual
`workflow_dispatch` runs always execute.

## Project Structure

```
{{.Name}}/
├── .reliant/    # Forge-managed conventions, skills, and project metadata
├── cmd/         # Application entrypoints
├── db/          # SQL migrations and sqlc queries
├── deploy/      # KCL deployment manifests
├── e2e/         # End-to-end tests (gated by the `e2e` build tag)
├── frontends/   # Frontend applications
├── gen/         # Generated protobuf code (not committed; run `forge generate`)
├── handlers/    # Service implementations
├── pkg/         # Shared Go packages (app wiring, middleware, config)
└── proto/       # Protocol buffer definitions (source of truth)
```